title: 820-00165 cycling 100ma -20ma
message: Had a bit of spillage around U5110, I replaced u5110 and surrounding component's. Board draws 100ma then drops back to 20ma. PP5V_S4RS3 is missing so is P5VS4RS3_EN (pulsing)

Bad pch?

title: 820-00165 cycling 100ma -20ma
message:
As all liquid damaged boards, I recommend to reball SMC.
Also check all SPI Bus Series Termination resistors and their traces.

title: 820-00165 cycling 100ma -20ma
message: I reballed Smc, then replaced it and all spi termniation resistors and lines to the bios chip are good. Seems when PP1V05_S0SW_PCH_HSIO is connected via U8005 then it starts cycling.
